{
  "version": "Notebook/1.0",
  "items": [
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "## Autovacuum monitoring\r\n\r\nThis troubleshooting guide assesses the health of autovacuum and vacuum on Azure Database for PostgreSQL Flexible Server. Autovacuum removes dead tuples to free disk space and improve query performance, and it updates the visibility map so PostgreSQL can skip pages that no longer contain outdated or deleted rows.\r\n\r\nAutovacuum also prevents transaction ID wraparound, which would otherwise stop the server from accepting writes. Use the sections below to identify bloat, blocked vacuums, throttling, and tuning opportunities before they become incidents.\r\n\r\n### Diagnostic steps\r\n\r\nFollow these steps in order to systematically diagnose the issue.\r\n\r\nStep | Description\r\n--- | ---\r\n**Analysis period** | Choose the time interval to analyze.\r\n**Database** | Choose the database to analyze. Select **All** for all databases on the server, or pick a specific database to narrow the analysis.\r\n**Bloat** | Review the bloat ratio for each database.\r\n**Tuples** | Compare live vs dead tuples, and counts of inserts, updates, and deletes.\r\n**Vacuum and analyze** | Track how many tables were vacuumed and analyzed in each database.\r\n**Autovacuum activity** | Track autovacuum run volume, durations, worker saturation, and per‑table activity.\r\n**Autovacuum per table** | Review autovacuum activity at the table level, including anti-wraparound runs and cancellations.\r\n**Enhanced metrics** | Track maximum transaction IDs in use and the oldest backend xmin.\r\n**Vacuum throttling overview** | Identify when cost-based delay settings are slowing autovacuum.\r\n**Insights** | Automatically detected autovacuum tuning opportunities and configuration warnings.\r\n**Configuration** | Review current autovacuum-related server parameters, their defaults, and which have been modified.\r\n\r\n### Scope and limits\r\n\r\n- Only databases and schemas with **more than 100 live tuples and more than 1,000 dead tuples** are shown. Counts here may not match the totals on your server.\r\n- The guide analyzes up to **30 databases** per server (**10** on the Burstable SKU), in order of database creation (OID).\r\n- When a server exceeds the database cap, a warning is displayed in the main view.",
        "style": "info"
      },
      "name": "autovacuum monitoring header"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "#### Start by setting the following parameters:"
      },
      "name": "parameters for the workbook"
    },
