      "customWidth": "33",
      "name": "avbarchartbyelapsedtime",
      "styleSettings": {
        "showBorder": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "#### Daily aggregated autovacuum history\r\n\r\nEach row summarizes autovacuum activity for one day on a specific table, including run count, anti-wraparound runs, average tuples removed, average non-removable dead tuples, average index scans per run, and average elapsed time.",
        "style": "info"
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "vacuumpertablehistory"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "Autovacuum History Grid view text"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "**Tip:** Select any row in the grid below to view every individual autovacuum run for that table on that day.",
        "style": "upsell"
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "vacuumpertablehistory"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "avpertablehistorySelectionHint"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "let graphgrain = 1d;\r\nlet dbFilter = '{Database}';\r\n{ParsedAutovacuumLogs}\r\n| where dbFilter == 'All' or database == dbFilter\r\n| summarize \r\n    ['vacuum count'] = count(),\r\n    ['anti-wraparound runs'] = countif(is_antiwraparound),\r\n    ['tuples removed'] = round(avg(tuples_removed)),\r\n    ['tuples remain'] = round(avg(tuples_remain)),\r\n    ['tuples dead but not removed'] = round(avg(tuples_dead_not_removed)),\r\n    ['index scans'] = round(avg(index_scans), 1),\r\n    ['elapsed time'] = round(avg(elapsed_time), 2)\r\n    by bin(TimeGenerated, graphgrain), database, schema, table\r\n| project-rename ['time generated'] = TimeGenerated\r\n| order by ['time generated'] desc",
        "size": 0,
        "exportedParameters": [
          {
            "fieldName": "time generated",
            "parameterName": "AVHistoryTime",
            "parameterType": 1
          },
          {
            "fieldName": "database",
            "parameterName": "AVHistoryDatabase",
            "parameterType": 1
          },
          {
            "fieldName": "schema",
            "parameterName": "AVHistorySchema",
            "parameterType": 1
          },
          {
            "fieldName": "table",
            "parameterName": "AVHistoryTable",
            "parameterType": 1
          },
          {
            "parameterName": "All",
            "parameterType": 1
          }
        ],
        "showExportToExcel": true,
        "queryType": 0,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Resource}"
        ],
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "time generated",
              "formatter": 6,
              "dateFormat": {
                "showUtcTime": true,
                "formatName": "shortDateTimePattern"
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "vacuum count",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples removed",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples remain",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples dead but not removed",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal",
                  "useGrouping": false
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "elapsed time",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 24,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples dead but nor removed",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "rowLimit": 10000,
          "filter": true
        },
        "sortBy": []
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "vacuumpertablehistory"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "avpertablehistory"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "let AVDate = todatetime('{AVHistoryTime}');\r\nlet AVDatabase = '{AVHistoryDatabase}';\r\nlet AVSchema = '{AVHistorySchema}';\r\nlet AVTable = '{AVHistoryTable}';\r\n{ParsedAutovacuumLogs}\r\n| where startofday(TimeGenerated) == startofday(AVDate)\r\n| where database == AVDatabase and schema == AVSchema and table == AVTable\r\n| project\r\n    ['time generated'] = TimeGenerated,\r\n    database, schema, table,\r\n    ['tuples removed'] = tuples_removed,\r\n    ['tuples remain'] = tuples_remain,\r\n    ['tuples dead but not removed'] = tuples_dead_not_removed,\r\n    ['index scans'] = index_scans,\r\n    ['elapsed time'] = elapsed_time,\r\n    ['anti-wraparound'] = is_antiwraparound,\r\n    ['autovacuum log'] = Message\r\n| order by ['time generated'] desc",
        "size": 0,
        "title": "Detailed autovacuum activity for {AVHistoryDatabase}.{AVHistorySchema}.{AVHistoryTable}",
        "showExportToExcel": true,
        "queryType": 0,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Resource}"
        ],
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "time generated",
              "formatter": 6,
              "dateFormat": {
                "showUtcTime": true,
                "formatName": "shortDateTimePattern"
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples removed",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples remain",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "tuples dead but not removed",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 17,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "elapsed time",
              "formatter": 0,
              "numberFormat": {
                "unit": 24,
                "options": {
                  "style": "decimal"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "rowLimit": 10000,
          "filter": true
        },
        "sortBy": []
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "vacuumpertablehistory"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "AVHistoryTime",
          "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
        }
      ],
      "name": "avpertablehistorysubgrid"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "| Column                       | Description                                                                                                                                   |\r\n|------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| tuples dead but not removed  | Rows that were dead but could not be cleaned up because an open transaction's snapshot might still need them. Persistent values indicate a vacuum blocker. |\r\n| anti-wraparound runs         | Vacuums that bypassed cost throttling to prevent transaction ID exhaustion. A non-zero value warrants investigation.                          |\r\n| index scans           | Number of index passes per vacuum run. Values above 1 indicate `maintenance_work_mem` is too small and vacuum is doing extra work.    |"
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "vacuumpertablehistory"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "AVHistoryGridColumnInfo"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "These metrics require the dynamic server parameter `metrics.collector_database_activity` to be enabled. No restart is required.\r\n\r\n#### Maximum Used Transaction IDs\r\n\r\nThe highest transaction ID (XID) currently in use on the server. PostgreSQL has approximately 2 billion usable XIDs before wraparound, after which the server stops accepting writes to protect data integrity.\r\n\r\n- **Healthy:** below 200 million.\r\n- **Investigate:** 200 million to 1 billion. Anti-wraparound vacuums are running. Review the **Autovacuum blockers troubleshooting guide** to find what is blocking routine cleanup.\r\n- **Critical:** above 1 billion. Set a metric alert at this level. On PostgreSQL 14 and later, the vacuum failsafe kicks in at `vacuum_failsafe_age` (default 1.6 billion) and bypasses cost throttling to prevent shutdown.\r\n\r\nSee the [PostgreSQL documentation on wraparound](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/routine-vacuuming.html#VACUUM-FOR-WRAPAROUND) for background.\r\n\r\n#### Oldest Backend Xmin\r\n\r\nThe oldest `xmin` horizon across all backends. Vacuum cannot remove any row version newer than this value, so a stalled `xmin` blocks dead tuple cleanup regardless of how often autovacuum runs.\r\n\r\n- **Healthy:** advances steadily with transaction throughput.\r\n- **Investigate:** flat or barely changing. Likely causes are a long-running transaction, an idle session in a transaction, an orphaned prepared transaction, or an inactive replication slot.\r\n- **Action:** use the **Autovacuum blockers** workbook to identify and resolve the blocker before bloat accumulates.",
        "style": "info"
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "txidmetric"
        }
      ],
      "name": "txid metric information"
    },
    {
      "type": 10,
      "content": {
        "chartId": "workbook0190696b-5f8a-4fc0-8c21-5bf6c6a9ece2",
        "version": "MetricsItem/2.0",
        "size": 0,
        "chartType": 2,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
