    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
        "groupType": "editable",
        "items": [
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### Vacuum throttling overview\r\n\r\nThis chart shows the number of `VacuumDelay` wait samples captured per interval. Each sample represents an autovacuum or manual vacuum worker that was paused by cost-based throttling. Sustained or spiking values indicate that vacuum operations are being slowed by `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay` and `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit` settings.\r\n\r\n**Data source:** `pgms_wait_sampling` (high-fidelity wait event sampling).",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "UseWaitSampling",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "vacuumdelayInfoWaitSampling"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let Start_Time = todatetime('{GlobalStartTime}');\r\nlet End_Time = todatetime('{GlobalEndTime}');\r\n{QueryStoreWaitSampling}\r\n| where EndTime >= Start_Time and EndTime <= End_Time\r\n| where Event == 'VacuumDelay'\r\n| make-series VacuumDelaySamples = sum(Calls) default=0 on EndTime from Start_Time to End_Time step {TimeRange:grain}",
              "size": 0,
              "title": "VacuumDelay wait samples over time",
              "timeBrushParameterName": "TimeRange",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
              "crossComponentResources": [
                "{Resource}"
              ],
              "visualization": "barchart",
              "chartSettings": {
                "showLegend": true
              }
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "UseWaitSampling",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "vacuumdelayWaitSampling"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### Vacuum throttling overview\r\n\r\nThis chart shows the number of sampled sessions observed in the `VacuumDelay` wait state. Each data point reflects a snapshot of `pg_stat_activity` collected approximately every 5 minutes. Elevated values indicate that vacuum workers are being throttled by cost-based delay settings.\r\n\r\n**Data source:** `pg_stat_activity` session snapshots (5 minute resolution).\r\n\r\n**Tip:** For higher resolution visibility into vacuum throttling, enable `pgms_wait_sampling.query_capture_mode` on the server and enable the `PostgreSQLFlexQueryStoreWaitStats` diagnostic log category.",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "UseWaitSampling",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "vacuumdelayInfoSessions"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let Start_Time = todatetime('{GlobalStartTime}');\r\nlet End_Time = todatetime('{GlobalEndTime}');\r\n{PostgreSQLFlexSessions}\r\n| where TimeGenerated >= Start_Time and TimeGenerated <= End_Time\r\n| where WaitEvent == \"VacuumDelay\"\r\n| make-series VacuumDelayCount = count() on TimeGenerated from Start_Time to End_Time step {TimeRange:grain}",
              "size": 0,
              "title": "VacuumDelay sessions over time",
              "timeBrushParameterName": "TimeRange",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
              "crossComponentResources": [
                "{Resource}"
              ],
              "visualization": "barchart",
              "chartSettings": {
                "showLegend": true
              }
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "UseWaitSampling",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "vacuumdelaySessions"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### Recommended actions\r\n\r\nReview the chart above before changing any parameters. Brief or occasional throttling is expected and does not require action. Consider tuning only when throttling is sustained or coincides with bloat growth, transaction ID age increases, or autovacuum failing to keep up.\r\n\r\nIf tuning is needed:\r\n\r\n- **Reduce the cost delay.** Lower `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay` to shorten the pause taken by each vacuum worker after reaching the cost limit. Start with small reductions and observe the impact.\r\n- **Increase the cost limit.** Raise `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit` to allow workers to perform more I/O work before being throttled. This is often more effective than lowering the delay.\r\n- **Target high-traffic tables.** Use per-table storage parameters (`autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay`, `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit`) to apply tighter tuning only on tables that need it, rather than changing server-wide defaults.\r\n- **Monitor after each change.** Adjust parameters incrementally and review this chart over the following days. Confirm that throttling has decreased without introducing CPU or I/O pressure on the server.",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "name": "vacuumdelayInfoRecommendations"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "vacuumdelay"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "IsServerPrimary",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "vacuumdelaygroup"
    },
    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
        "groupType": "editable",
        "items": [
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "crossComponentResources": [
                "{Resource}"
              ],
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "01e7f55b-ab8c-4908-bce3-01dc9daa1ef4",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "IndexVacuumInsight",
                  "type": 1,
                  "query": "// Autovacuum Tuning Opportunities (with full commentary and friendly headers)\r\n// Identifies tables where autovacuum needed multiple index-cleanup phases (tuning candidates).\r\n\r\n// ------------------------\r\n// Tunables\r\n// ------------------------\r\nlet multi_scan_threshold  = 1;\r\nlet min_runs              = 3;\r\nlet top_n_tables          = 5;\r\nlet TimeStart             = todatetime('{GlobalStartTime}');\r\nlet TimeEnd               = todatetime('{GlobalEndTime}');\r\n\r\n// ------------------------\r\n// Base extraction\r\n// ------------------------\r\nlet base = materialize(\r\n    {PostgreSQLLogs}\r\n    | where TimeGenerated between (TimeStart .. TimeEnd)\r\n    | where Message contains \"automatic vacuum of table\"\r\n    | extend database = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table\\s+\"\"([^.\"\"]+)\\.([^.]+)\\.([^\"\"]+)\"\"\", 1, Message),\r\n             schema   = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table\\s+\"\"([^.\"\"]+)\\.([^.]+)\\.([^\"\"]+)\"\"\", 2, Message),\r\n             table    = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table\\s+\"\"([^.\"\"]+)\\.([^.]+)\\.([^\"\"]+)\"\"\", 3, Message)\r\n    | where database !in ('azure_sys','azure_maintenance','template0','template1')\r\n    | extend index_scans = coalesce(toint(extract(@\"index scan[s]?:\\s*(\\d+)\", 1, Message)), 0),\r\n             elapsed_s   = todouble(extract(@\"elapsed:\\s*([0-9]+(?:\\.[0-9]+)?)\\s*s\", 1, Message))\r\n);\r\n\r\n// ------------------------\r\n// Per-run projection\r\n// ------------------------\r\nlet per_run =\r\n    base\r\n    | project database, schema, table, TimeGenerated, index_scans, elapsed_s;\r\n\r\n// ------------------------\r\n// Per-table rollup\r\n// ------------------------\r\nlet per_table_raw =\r\n    per_run\r\n    | summarize\r\n        total_vacuum_count = count(),\r\n        index_vacuum_count = countif(index_scans > multi_scan_threshold),\r\n        max_index_vacuum_count_per_run = max(index_scans),\r\n        avg_duration_s = round(avg(elapsed_s), 2),\r\n        p95_duration_s = round(percentile(elapsed_s, 95), 2)\r\n      by database, schema, table;\r\n\r\nlet per_table =\r\n    per_table_raw\r\n    | extend index_vacuum_pct = iff(total_vacuum_count == 0, 0.0, toreal(index_vacuum_count) / toreal(total_vacuum_count));\r\n\r\n// ------------------------\r\n// Heuristic: tuning candidates\r\n// ------------------------\r\nlet pressure_tables =\r\n    per_table\r\n    | where total_vacuum_count >= min_runs\r\n    | where max_index_vacuum_count_per_run > multi_scan_threshold;\r\n\r\nlet has_pressure = toscalar(pressure_tables | summarize cnt = count()) > 0;\r\n\r\n// ------------------------\r\n// Markdown Output\r\n// ------------------------\r\nlet top_rows = materialize(\r\n    pressure_tables\r\n    | order by p95_duration_s desc, index_vacuum_count desc, max_index_vacuum_count_per_run desc\r\n    | take top_n_tables\r\n    | project line = strcat(\r\n        \"| \", database, \".\", schema, \".\", table, \" | \",\r\n        tostring(total_vacuum_count), \" | \",\r\n        tostring(index_vacuum_count), \" | \",\r\n        tostring(max_index_vacuum_count_per_run), \" | \",\r\n        tostring(avg_duration_s), \" | \",\r\n        tostring(p95_duration_s), \" |\"\r\n    )\r\n);\r\n\r\nlet top_body = toscalar(top_rows | summarize md = strcat_array(make_list(line), \"\\n\"));\r\n\r\nlet full_md = strcat_array(\r\n    pack_array(\r\n        \"### Autovacuum tuning opportunities\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"**What this shows**\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"Tables listed below experienced either a single autovacuum run with multiple index-cleanup passes or a consistent pattern of such runs.\",  \r\n        \"\\n This behavior typically indicates that **maintenance_work_mem** or **autovacuum_work_mem** is set too low, causing PostgreSQL to perform extra cleanup cycles that increase vacuum duration.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"**Top 5 tables shown below are ordered by highest P95 duration and index vacuum count.**\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"| Table | Total VACUUM Runs | Runs with Multiple Index Passes | Max Index VACUUM Count per Run | Avg Duration (s) | P95 Duration (s) |\\n\",\r\n        \"|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\\n\",\r\n        iif(strlen(top_body) == 0, \"| (none) | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 0 |\\n\", top_body), \"\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"**Column Summary**\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Table**: Fully qualified name of the table (database.schema.table).\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Total VACUUM Runs**: Number of autovacuum runs observed for the table.\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Runs with Multiple Index Passes**: Number of runs where multiple index-cleanup phases were needed.\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Max Index VACUUM Count per Run**: Maximum number of index scans observed in a single autovacuum run.\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Avg Duration (s)**: Average duration of autovacuum runs in seconds.\\n\",\r\n        \"- **P95 Duration (s)**: 95th percentile of autovacuum durations in seconds.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"**Why it matters**\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"Extra index-cleanup passes = longer VACUUMs, more contention.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"**Recommendations**\\n\",\r\n        \"1. Increase **maintenance_work_mem** or **autovacuum_work_mem** for autovacuum workers and monitor if index vacuum count and p95 duration drop.\\n\",\r\n        \"2. If symptoms persist, consider **REINDEX CONCURRENTLY**.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"**Recommendation to upgrade to PostgreSQL 17 or later**\\n\\n\",\r\n\"PostgreSQL 17 introduced adaptive radix trees for dead tuple storage and more responsive autovacuum config reloads. PostgreSQL 18 builds on that with eager freezing, an `autovacuum_vacuum_max_threshold` cap, and dynamic `autovacuum_max_workers`. Upgrading reduces the need for extra index vacuum phases and improves responsiveness under high churn.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Efficient Memory Usage**: VACUUM now uses adaptive radix trees for dead tuple storage, significantly improving memory efficiency and reducing cleanup cycles even with lower **maintenance_work_mem**.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"- **Responsive Configuration Reloads**: Autovacuum workers now reload configuration changes more responsively, checking for updates roughly once per block. This enables dynamic tuning of cost-based parameters mid-process.\\n\\n\",\r\n        \"These enhancements reduce the need for multiple index vacuum phases and improve responsiveness under high-concurrency workloads, making PostgreSQL 17 a compelling upgrade for environments focused on performance and maintainability.\\n\"\r\n    ),\r\n    \"\"\r\n);\r\n\r\n\r\nprint InsightMD = iif(has_pressure, full_md, \"\")",
                  "crossComponentResources": [
                    "{Resource}"
                  ],
                  "isHiddenWhenLocked": true,
                  "queryType": 0,
                  "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers"
                },
                {
                  "id": "65fabd6a-f762-4e14-a155-d036115adfb2",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "CostlimitThrottleInsight",
                  "type": 1,
                  "query": "// =======================\r\n// Adjustable Parameters\r\n// =======================\r\nlet Start_Time = todatetime('{GlobalStartTime}');\r\nlet End_Time   = todatetime('{GlobalEndTime}');\r\n\r\n// Page cost parameters (replace with your server values)\r\nlet VacuumCostPageHit   = todouble({vacuum_cost_page_hit});   // e.g., 1\r\nlet VacuumCostPageMiss  = todouble({vacuum_cost_page_miss});  // e.g., 2\r\nlet VacuumCostPageDirty = todouble({vacuum_cost_page_dirty}); // e.g., 20\r\n\r\n// Server-side throttling params (replace with your server values)\r\nlet AutoVacuumCostLimit = todouble({fetch_autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit});\r\nlet VacuumCostLimitBase = todouble({fetch_vacuum_cost_limit});\r\nlet VacuumCostLimit = iif(AutoVacuumCostLimit == -1, VacuumCostLimitBase, AutoVacuumCostLimit);\r\nlet VacuumCostDelayMs = todouble({fetch_autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay});    // numeric, e.g., 0..20\r\n\r\n// Insight thresholds\r\nlet TargetSleepPct = todouble(10.0);              // Target: sleep ≤ 10% of elapsed\r\nlet ThrottleBindingThresholdPct = todouble(20.0); // Flag if P95 sleep% ≥ 20%\r\nlet MinRuns = toint(1); // Minimum number of runs per table to include\r\n\r\n// =======================\r\n// Parse autovacuum runs from logs\r\n// =======================\r\nlet BaseVacuumRuns =\r\n{PostgreSQLLogs}\r\n| where TimeGenerated between (Start_Time .. End_Time)\r\n| where Message has \"automatic vacuum of table\"\r\n| extend Msg = replace_regex(Message, @\"\\r?\\n\", \" \")  // flatten multiline\r\n| extend TableName = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table \\\"\"([^\\\\\"\"]+)\\\"\"\", 1, Msg)\r\n| extend database = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table\\s+\"\"([^.\"\"]+)\\.([^.]+)\\.([^\"\"]+)\"\"\", 1, Message),\r\n             schema   = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table\\s+\"\"([^.\"\"]+)\\.([^.]+)\\.([^\"\"]+)\"\"\", 2, Message),\r\n             table    = extract(@\"automatic vacuum of table\\s+\"\"([^.\"\"]+)\\.([^.]+)\\.([^\"\"]+)\"\"\", 3, Message)\r\n| where database !in (\"azure_sys\", \"azure_maintenance\",\"template0\",\"template1\")\r\n| where schema !in (\"pg_catalog\")\r\n// Buffer usage: hits, misses, dirtied\r\n| extend Hits    = todouble(extract(@\"buffer usage:\\s+(\\d+)\\s+hits\", 1, Msg))\r\n| extend Misses  = todouble(extract(@\"buffer usage:\\s+\\d+\\s+hits,\\s+(\\d+)\\s+misses\", 1, Msg))\r\n| extend Dirtied = todouble(extract(@\"buffer usage:\\s+\\d+\\s+hits,\\s+\\d+\\s+misses,\\s+(\\d+)\\s+dirtied\", 1, Msg))\r\n// system usage: CPU and elapsed\r\n| extend CPUUserS = todouble(extract(@\"CPU:\\s*user:\\s*([0-9\\.]+)\\s*s\", 1, Msg))\r\n| extend CPUSysS  = todouble(extract(@\"CPU:[^,]+,\\s*system:\\s*([0-9\\.]+)\\s*s\", 1, Msg))\r\n| extend ElapsedS = todouble(extract(@\"elapsed:\\s*([0-9\\.]+)\\s*s\", 1, Msg))\r\n| extend ElapsedMs = ElapsedS * 1000.0, CPUUserMs = CPUUserS * 1000.0, CPUSysMs = CPUSysS * 1000.0\r\n| where isnotempty(TableName) and isnotnull(ElapsedS)\r\n// =======================\r\n// Cost math and throttling estimation\r\n// =======================\r\n| extend TotalCostUnits = (Hits * VacuumCostPageHit) + (Misses * VacuumCostPageMiss) + (Dirtied * VacuumCostPageDirty)\r\n| extend EstSleepMs = iif(VacuumCostLimit > 0 and VacuumCostDelayMs > 0, (TotalCostUnits / VacuumCostLimit) * VacuumCostDelayMs, real(null))\r\n| extend SleepPct = iif(ElapsedMs > 0 and isnotnull(EstSleepMs), 100.0 * EstSleepMs / ElapsedMs, real(null))\r\n| extend AllowedCostRatePerSec  = iif(VacuumCostDelayMs > 0, 1000.0 * VacuumCostLimit / VacuumCostDelayMs, real(null))\r\n| extend ObservedCostRatePerSec = iif(ElapsedS > 0, TotalCostUnits / ElapsedS, real(null))\r\n| extend SleepVsCPU = iif((CPUUserMs + CPUSysMs) > 0, EstSleepMs / (CPUUserMs + CPUSysMs), real(null))\r\n// Recommended cost limit per run to keep sleep ≤ TargetSleepPct of elapsed\r\n| extend RecLimitPerRun = iif(\r\n    ElapsedMs > 0 and VacuumCostDelayMs > 0 and TotalCostUnits > 0,\r\n    tolong( ceiling( (TotalCostUnits * VacuumCostDelayMs) / ((TargetSleepPct/100.0) * ElapsedMs) ) ),\r\n    long(null)\r\n  )\r\n| project TimeGenerated, TableName, Hits, Misses, Dirtied, CPUUserS, CPUSysS, ElapsedS,\r\n          TotalCostUnits, EstSleepMs, SleepPct, AllowedCostRatePerSec, ObservedCostRatePerSec, SleepVsCPU, RecLimitPerRun;\r\n\r\n// =======================\r\n// Table-level rollup\r\n// =======================\r\nlet PerTable =\r\nBaseVacuumRuns\r\n| summarize Runs = count(),\r\n            P95ElapsedS = percentile(ElapsedS, 95),\r\n            AvgElapsedS = avg(ElapsedS),\r\n            P95SleepPct = percentile(SleepPct, 95),\r\n            AvgSleepPct = avg(SleepPct),\r\n            P95ObservedCostRate = percentile(ObservedCostRatePerSec, 95),\r\n            AvgObservedCostRate = avg(ObservedCostRatePerSec),\r\n            P95SleepVsCPU = percentile(SleepVsCPU, 95),\r\n            P95RecLimit = percentile(RecLimitPerRun, 95)\r\n  by TableName\r\n| where Runs >= MinRuns\r\n| extend EstSleepPctWithSuggested = TargetSleepPct\r\n| extend BenefitPct = iif(isnotnull(P95SleepPct), round(P95SleepPct - TargetSleepPct, 1), real(null))\r\n| extend BenefitPctClamped = iif(isnull(BenefitPct), real(null), iif(BenefitPct < 0, 0.0, BenefitPct))\r\n| extend Conservative = iif(P95SleepPct >= ThrottleBindingThresholdPct or P95SleepVsCPU >= 1.0, 1, 0);\r\n\r\n// =======================\r\n// Markdown pieces\r\n// =======================\r\nlet Header = strcat(\r\n  \"### Autovacuum cost-limit conservativeness\\n\\n\",\r\n  \"**Assumptions:** `vacuum_cost_page_hit`=\", tostring(VacuumCostPageHit),\r\n  \", `vacuum_cost_page_miss`=\", tostring(VacuumCostPageMiss),\r\n  \", `vacuum_cost_page_dirty`=\", tostring(VacuumCostPageDirty),\r\n  \", `autovacuum_cost_limit`=\", tostring(VacuumCostLimit),\r\n  \", `autovacuum_cost_delay`=\", tostring(VacuumCostDelayMs), \"ms\",\r\n  \", target sleep ≤ \", tostring(TargetSleepPct), \"% of elapsed.\\n\\n\"\r\n);\r\n\r\n// --- NEW: Suggestion/Action text per table (based on conservativeness + delay) is computed in the TopConservative section\r\nlet TopConservative =\r\nPerTable\r\n| where BenefitPctClamped > 0\r\n| order by BenefitPctClamped desc, P95SleepPct desc\r\n| take 5\r\n| extend Alert = iif(Conservative == 1, \"🚩\", \"\")\r\n| extend SuggestionAction = iif(\r\n      Conservative == 1,\r\n      iif(VacuumCostDelayMs > 2.0,\r\n          \"First, set autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay to 2 ms and monitor; then gradually raise autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit by 100 each step.\",\r\n          \"Increase server-side autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit by +100 per iteration.\"\r\n      ),\r\n      \"—\"\r\n  )\r\n| extend Row = strcat(\"| \", Alert, \" \", TableName,\r\n                      \" | \", tostring(Runs),\r\n                      \" | \", tostring(round(P95ElapsedS, 2)), \"s\",\r\n                      \" | \", tostring(round(P95SleepPct, 1)), \"%\",\r\n                      \" | \", SuggestionAction, \" |\")\r\n| summarize Body = strcat_array(make_list(Row), \"\\n\");\r\n\r\nlet ColumnSummary = strcat(\r\n  \"**📊 Column Summary**\\n\\n\",\r\n  \"- **Table**: Schema-qualified table name parsed from autovacuum logs. A red flag (🚩) indicates likely conservative throttling.\\n\",\r\n  \"- **Runs**: Number of autovacuum executions observed in the selected time window.\\n\",\r\n  \"- **P95 Elapsed**: 95th percentile of total elapsed time per run (seconds).\\n\",\r\n  \"- **P95 Est. Sleep%**: Estimated sleep time due to cost-based throttling as a percentage of total elapsed time (P95).\\n\",\r\n  \"- **Suggestion/Action**: If conservative throttling is detected and `autovacuum_cost_delay` > 2 ms, reduce it to 2 ms first; then increase server-side `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit` by +100 per iteration. If delay ≤ 2 ms, increase `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit` by +100 per iteration.\\n\",\r\n  \"- **🚩 Alert Criteria**: Triggered when `P95 Est. Sleep%` ≥ \", tostring(ThrottleBindingThresholdPct), \"% or `Sleep vs CPU` ≥ 1.0, indicating strong throttling pressure.\\n\"\r\n);\r\n\r\nlet Guidance = strcat(\r\n  \"**📘 Guidance**\\n\\n\",\r\n  \"**Estimation Logic**: Total cost units = hits × hit_cost + misses × miss_cost + dirtied × dirty_cost. \",\r\n  \"Estimated sleep = (total_cost / cost_limit) × cost_delay. If sleep is a large share of elapsed time, the cost limit is likely conservative.\\n\\n\",\r\n  \"**Notes**:\\n\",\r\n  \"- High `Sleep vs CPU` strengthens the case for increasing `autovacuum_cost_limit` or reducing `autovacuum_cost_delay`.\\n\",\r\n  \"- Prefer per-table reloptions when only a few tables are affected.\\n\",\r\n  \"- **Before increasing `autovacuum_cost_limit`, check `autovacuum_cost_delay`:** If the current delay is higher than 2 ms, try reducing it first (down to 2 ms) before raising the cost limit. This often yields better balance between throughput and I/O impact.\\n\\n\",\r\n  \"**⚠️ Caution**: Higher cost limits reduce throttling but may increase I/O and CPU pressure, affecting concurrent workloads. \",\r\n  \"Apply changes gradually, test in non-production environments, and monitor I/O latency, CPU usage.\\n\\n\",\r\n  \"&gt; **Note**: This insight does **not** account for:\\n\",\r\n  \"&gt; - Concurrent autovacuum workers: Multiple workers may amplify cost pressure.\\n\",\r\n  \"&gt; - Per-table autovacuum settings: Table-specific overrides are not reflected in global recommendations.\\n\"\r\n);\r\n\r\n// =======================\r\n// Final Markdown table\r\n// =======================\r\nPerTable\r\n| where BenefitPctClamped > 0\r\n| summarize CountTables = count()\r\n| extend Markdown = iif(CountTables == 0, \"\", strcat(\r\n    Header,\r\n    \"#### Top 5 Tables Likely Throttled by Cost-Based Delay (with Benefit)\\n\\n\",\r\n    \"| Table | Runs | P95 Elapsed | P95 Est. Sleep% | Suggestion/Action |\\n\",\r\n    \"|------|-----:|------------:|-----------------:|-------------------|\\n\",\r\n    toscalar(TopConservative | project Body),\r\n    \"\\n\\n\", ColumnSummary,\r\n    \"\\n\\n\", Guidance\r\n))\r\n| project Markdown\r\n| where isnotempty(Markdown)",
                  "crossComponentResources": [
                    "{Resource}"
                  ],
                  "isHiddenWhenLocked": true,
                  "queryType": 0,
                  "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers"
                },
                {
                  "id": "7d4a8b2e-3c5f-4a91-bd6e-2f9c8a1b3d4e",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "ConfigRisksInsight",
                  "type": 1,
                  "query": "let configs = materialize(\r\n    print raw = dynamic({GetInsightParameters})\r\n    | mv-expand item = raw.value\r\n    | project name = tostring(item.name),\r\n              v = tostring(item.properties.value),\r\n              d = tostring(item.properties.defaultValue),\r\n              unit = tostring(item.properties.unit)\r\n);\r\nlet single_rules = configs\r\n| extend Reason = case(\r\n    name == \"autovacuum\" and tolower(v) == \"off\",                          \"Autovacuum is disabled. The server will not automatically maintain tables. Set to `on` unless you have a documented reason to disable it.\",\r\n    name == \"log_autovacuum_min_duration\" and toint(v) == -1,              \"Autovacuum activity is not being logged. The Autovacuum per table tab will appear empty. Set to a non-negative value (10000 ms recommended).\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay\" and todouble(v) == 0,           \"Cost-based throttling is disabled (`autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay = 0`). Autovacuum will consume I/O and CPU without pause. This is acceptable on fast storage (NVMe, PG 18+ with streaming I/O) but should be verified as intentional.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay\" and todouble(v) > 20,           \"Cost delay is high, causing aggressive throttling. Consider reducing to 2 ms and adjusting `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit` instead.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_vacuum_scale_factor\" and todouble(v) > 0.2,        \"Vacuum scale factor is high. Tables accumulate more dead tuples before being vacuumed, increasing bloat risk. Default is 0.2.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_analyze_scale_factor\" and todouble(v) > 0.1,       \"Analyze scale factor is high. Statistics will be updated less frequently and may affect query plan quality. Default is 0.1.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_max_workers\" and tolong(v) < 3,                    \"Autovacuum worker count is below the default of 3. The server may struggle to keep up with multiple busy tables.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_max_workers\" and tolong(v) > 10,                   \"Autovacuum worker count is above 10. Very high counts can cause excessive vacuum activity and resource pressure.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_naptime\" and tolong(v) > 60,                       \"Autovacuum nap time is above the default of 60 seconds. The server checks for vacuum candidates less frequently, delaying cleanup.\",\r\n    name == \"autovacuum_freeze_max_age\" and tolong(v) > 1500000000,        \"Anti-wraparound vacuum trigger is set very high. The server may approach transaction ID exhaustion before forced vacuum kicks in.\",\r\n    \"\")\r\n| where isnotempty(Reason)\r\n| extend Value = iif(isnotempty(unit), strcat(v, ' ', unit), v)\r\n| project Parameter = name, Value, Reason;\r\nlet correlated_rule = materialize(\r\n    configs\r\n    | where name in (\"autovacuum_max_workers\", \"autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit\", \"vacuum_cost_limit\", \"autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay\")\r\n    | summarize vbag = make_bag(pack(name, v)), dbag = make_bag(pack(name, d))\r\n    | extend amw  = tolong(vbag.autovacuum_max_workers),\r\n             avcl = tolong(vbag.autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit),\r\n             avcld = tolong(dbag.autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit),\r\n             vcl  = tolong(vbag.vacuum_cost_limit),\r\n             vcld = tolong(dbag.vacuum_cost_limit),\r\n             avcd = todouble(vbag.autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay)\r\n    | where amw >= 5 and amw <= 10 and avcd > 0 and avcl == avcld and vcl == vcld\r\n    | project Parameter = \"autovacuum_max_workers + cost limits\",\r\n              Value = strcat(\"workers=\", tostring(amw), \", cost_limit at default\"),\r\n              Reason = \"Worker count is elevated while `autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit` and `vacuum_cost_limit` remain at defaults. Cost limits are split across workers, so adding workers without raising cost limits slows each worker.\"\r\n);\r\nlet all_rules = union single_rules, correlated_rule;\r\nlet rule_count = toscalar(all_rules | summarize count());\r\nlet rows_md = toscalar(\r\n    all_rules\r\n    | project line = strcat(\"| `\", Parameter, \"` | \", Value, \" | \", Reason, \" |\")\r\n    | summarize body = strcat_array(make_list(line), \"\\n\")\r\n);\r\nlet full_md = strcat(\r\n    \"### Autovacuum configuration risks\\n\\n\",\r\n    \"**What this shows**\\n\\n\",\r\n    \"Server-level autovacuum parameters set to values that may slow, disable, or destabilize autovacuum. Review each entry below.\\n\\n\",\r\n    \"| Parameter | Current value | Reason |\\n\",\r\n    \"|---|---|---|\\n\",\r\n    rows_md,\r\n    \"\\n\\n\",\r\n    \"**Recommendations**\\n\\n\",\r\n    \"- Review each flagged value and confirm it is still intentional.\\n\",\r\n    \"- Defaults, descriptions, and per-version applicability are available in the **Configuration** tab.\\n\",\r\n    \"- For correlated cost-limit and worker tuning, see the recommendations alongside each row.\\n\"\r\n);\r\nprint AggressiveConfigInsight = iif(rule_count > 0, full_md, \"\")",
                  "crossComponentResources": [
                    "{Resource}"
                  ],
                  "isHiddenWhenLocked": true,
                  "queryType": 0,
                  "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers"
                }
              ],
              "style": "pills",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "x",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "y"
            },
            "name": "insightsparameters"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "{CostlimitThrottleInsight}",
              "style": "warning"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "CostlimitThrottleInsight",
              "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
            },
            "name": "CostlimitThrottleInsight"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "{IndexVacuumInsight}",
              "style": "warning"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "IndexVacuumInsight",
                "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "IsAutovcuumWorkMemHigh",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              }
            ],
            "name": "IndexVacuumInsight"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "{ConfigRisksInsight}",
              "style": "warning"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "ConfigRisksInsight",
              "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
            },
            "name": "AggressiveConfigInsight"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "#### No insights available for the selected time range.",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "IndexVacuumInsight",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "CostlimitThrottleInsight",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "ConfigRisksInsight",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo"
              }
            ],
            "name": "NoInsightMessage"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "insights"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "IsServerPrimary",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "InsightsGroup"
    },
    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
        "groupType": "editable",
        "items": [
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### Autovacuum configuration\r\n\r\nReview current autovacuum-related server parameters, their defaults, and which have been modified from PostgreSQL defaults. Use this tab to verify settings against the autovacuum activity observed in the other tabs.",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "name": "avconfigSectionIntro"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let descriptions = datatable(ParamName:string, MinPgVersion:int)\r\n[\r\n  'autovacuum', 0, 'autovacuum_naptime', 0, 'log_autovacuum_min_duration', 0,\r\n  'autovacuum_max_workers', 0, 'autovacuum_worker_slots', 18, 'autovacuum_work_mem', 0,\r\n  'maintenance_work_mem', 0, 'vacuum_buffer_usage_limit', 16,\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_threshold', 0, 'autovacuum_vacuum_scale_factor', 0,\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_max_threshold', 18, 'autovacuum_vacuum_insert_threshold', 13,\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_insert_scale_factor', 13, 'autovacuum_analyze_threshold', 0,\r\n  'autovacuum_analyze_scale_factor', 0, 'autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit', 0,\r\n  'vacuum_cost_limit', 0, 'autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay', 0,\r\n  'autovacuum_freeze_max_age', 0, 'autovacuum_multixact_freeze_max_age', 0,\r\n  'vacuum_failsafe_age', 14, 'vacuum_multixact_failsafe_age', 14,\r\n  'vacuum_max_eager_freeze_failure_rate', 18, 'vacuum_truncate', 18\r\n];\r\nlet configs = materialize(\r\n    print raw = dynamic({GetInsightParameters})\r\n    | mv-expand item = raw.value\r\n    | project name = tostring(item.name),\r\n              v = tostring(item.properties.value),\r\n              d = tostring(item.properties.defaultValue)\r\n);\r\nlet summary = configs\r\n| join kind=inner descriptions on $left.name == $right.ParamName\r\n| extend Modified = v != d\r\n| summarize\r\n    Total = count(),\r\n    AtDefault = countif(not(Modified)),\r\n    ModifiedCount = countif(Modified);\r\nlet aggressive = toscalar(\r\n    configs\r\n    | extend isAggressive = case(\r\n        name == \"autovacuum\"                     and tolower(v) == \"off\", true,\r\n        name == \"log_autovacuum_min_duration\"    and toint(v) == -1, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay\"   and todouble(v) == 0, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay\"   and todouble(v) > 20, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_vacuum_scale_factor\" and todouble(v) > 0.2, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_analyze_scale_factor\" and todouble(v) > 0.1, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_max_workers\"         and tolong(v) < 3, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_max_workers\"         and tolong(v) > 10, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_naptime\"             and tolong(v) > 60, true,\r\n        name == \"autovacuum_freeze_max_age\"      and tolong(v) > 1500000000, true,\r\n        false)\r\n    | summarize countif(isAggressive));\r\nsummary\r\n| project Metric = 'Parameters reviewed', Value = todouble(Total),         Tooltip = 'Total autovacuum-related parameters covered by this workbook.',                                                                                                Order = 1\r\n| union (summary | project Metric = 'At defaults',         Value = todouble(AtDefault),     Tooltip = 'Parameters currently set to the PostgreSQL default value.',                                                                                                Order = 2)\r\n| union (summary | project Metric = 'Modified',            Value = todouble(ModifiedCount), Tooltip = 'Parameters explicitly modified from the PostgreSQL default. Review whether each change is still intentional.',                                            Order = 3)\r\n| union (summary | project Metric = 'Configuration risks', Value = todouble(aggressive),    Tooltip = 'Server parameters set to values that may slow or destabilize autovacuum. See the Insights tab for details.', Order = 4)\r\n| order by Order asc\r\n| project Metric, Value, Tooltip",
              "size": 4,
              "title": "Configuration overview",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
              "crossComponentResources": [
                "{Resource}"
              ],
              "visualization": "tiles",
              "tileSettings": {
                "titleContent": {
                  "columnMatch": "Metric",
                  "formatter": 1
                },
                "leftContent": {
                  "columnMatch": "Value",
                  "formatter": 12,
                  "formatOptions": {
                    "palette": "auto"
                  },
                  "numberFormat": {
                    "unit": 17,
                    "options": {
                      "style": "decimal",
                      "maximumFractionDigits": 0,
                      "useGrouping": true
                    }
                  }
                },
                "subtitleContent": {
                  "columnMatch": "Tooltip",
                  "formatter": 1
                },
                "showBorder": true
              }
            },
            "name": "avconfigKPIStrip"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let descriptions = datatable(ParamName:string, Category:string, MinPgVersion:int, Description:string)\r\n[\r\n  'autovacuum', 'General', 0, 'Master switch. When off, autovacuum does not run (except to prevent wraparound).',\r\n  'autovacuum_naptime', 'General', 0, 'Minimum delay between autovacuum runs on any given database.',\r\n  'log_autovacuum_min_duration', 'General', 0, 'Logs autovacuum runs that exceed this duration. -1 disables logging. Recommended: 10000 (10 seconds) for ongoing monitoring.',\r\n  'autovacuum_max_workers', 'Workers', 0, 'Maximum number of autovacuum worker processes that can run concurrently. PG 18+: reloadable without restart when worker slots are pre-allocated.',\r\n  'autovacuum_worker_slots', 'Workers', 18, 'PG 18+: pre-allocated worker slots that allow autovacuum_max_workers to be raised without a server restart.',\r\n  'autovacuum_work_mem', 'Workers', 0, 'Memory per autovacuum worker. -1 falls back to maintenance_work_mem.',\r\n  'maintenance_work_mem', 'Workers', 0, 'Memory used by VACUUM, CREATE INDEX, and ALTER TABLE. Caps autovacuum_work_mem when that is -1.',\r\n  'vacuum_buffer_usage_limit', 'Memory', 16, 'Limits the shared buffer ring used by VACUUM (PG 16+).',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_threshold', 'Vacuum trigger', 0, 'Minimum dead tuples before a table is autovacuumed.',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_scale_factor', 'Vacuum trigger', 0, 'Fraction of table rows added to the threshold to decide when to vacuum.',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_max_threshold', 'Vacuum trigger', 18, 'PG 18+: caps the scale-factor-derived threshold so very large tables do not wait excessively to be vacuumed.',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_insert_threshold', 'Vacuum trigger', 13, 'Minimum inserted tuples before an insert-only autovacuum runs (PG 13+).',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_insert_scale_factor', 'Vacuum trigger', 13, 'Fraction of inserts added to the insert threshold (PG 13+).',\r\n  'autovacuum_analyze_threshold', 'Analyze trigger', 0, 'Minimum tuple changes before a table is auto-analyzed.',\r\n  'autovacuum_analyze_scale_factor', 'Analyze trigger', 0, 'Fraction of table rows added to the analyze threshold.',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit', 'Cost-based throttling', 0, 'Cost accumulated before a worker sleeps. -1 inherits vacuum_cost_limit.',\r\n  'vacuum_cost_limit', 'Cost-based throttling', 0, 'Base cost limit used when autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit is -1.',\r\n  'autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay', 'Cost-based throttling', 0, 'Sleep time after a worker hits the cost limit. Higher value slows vacuum.',\r\n  'autovacuum_freeze_max_age', 'Wraparound protection', 0, 'Table age (XIDs) at which forced anti-wraparound autovacuum kicks in.',\r\n  'autovacuum_multixact_freeze_max_age', 'Wraparound protection', 0, 'Multixact age that triggers forced anti-wraparound autovacuum.',\r\n  'vacuum_failsafe_age', 'Wraparound protection', 14, 'PG 14+: XID age at which VACUUM enters failsafe mode, skipping index vacuuming and cost-based delays to prevent imminent wraparound.',\r\n  'vacuum_multixact_failsafe_age', 'Wraparound protection', 14, 'PG 14+: multixact age that triggers failsafe mode during VACUUM.',\r\n  'vacuum_max_eager_freeze_failure_rate', 'Eager freezing', 18, 'PG 18+: allows non-aggressive vacuums to freeze all-visible pages proactively, smoothing wraparound pressure.',\r\n  'vacuum_truncate', 'Truncate', 18, 'PG 18+: GUC controlling end-of-vacuum truncate. When off, skips the truncate step server-wide to avoid AccessExclusiveLock contention.'\r\n];\r\nprint raw = dynamic({GetInsightParameters})\r\n| mv-expand item = raw.value\r\n| extend ParamName = tostring(item.name)\r\n| join kind=inner descriptions on ParamName\r\n| extend Unit = tostring(item.properties.unit)\r\n| extend Current = tostring(item.properties.value),\r\n         Default = tostring(item.properties.defaultValue)\r\n| extend Modified = iif(Current != Default, 'Yes', '')\r\n| extend AppliesTo = iif(MinPgVersion == 0, 'All versions', strcat('PG ', tostring(MinPgVersion), '+'))\r\n| project Category, Parameter = ParamName, Current, Default, Unit, Modified, AppliesTo, Description\r\n| order by Category asc, Parameter asc",
              "size": 0,
              "title": "Autovacuum current configuration",
              "showExportToExcel": true,
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.dbforpostgresql/flexibleservers",
              "crossComponentResources": [
                "{Resource}"
              ],
              "visualization": "table",
              "gridSettings": {
                "formatters": [
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Category",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Parameter",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Current",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Default",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Unit",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Modified",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "AppliesTo",
                    "formatter": 1
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Description",
                    "formatter": 1
                  }
                ],
                "rowLimit": 1000,
                "filter": true,
                "hierarchySettings": {
                  "treeType": 1,
                  "groupBy": [
                    "Category"
                  ],
                  "expandTopLevel": true
                }
              },
              "sortBy": []
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "IsServerPrimary",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "tab",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "config"
              }
            ],
            "name": "avconfiguration",
            "styleSettings": {
              "showBorder": true
            }
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "**Note:** The values above are server-level. PostgreSQL also supports per-table autovacuum settings via storage parameters (`ALTER TABLE ... SET (autovacuum_...)`). When set, table-level values take precedence over the server-level values shown here. Use `pg_class.reloptions` or `pg_stat_user_tables` to identify tables with custom settings.",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "IsServerPrimary",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "tab",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "config"
              }
            ],
            "name": "autovacuum configuration note"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditionalVisibilities": [
        {
          "parameterName": "tab",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "config"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "IsServerPrimary",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        },
        {
          "parameterName": "QualifiedDatabasesCount",
          "comparison": "isEqualTo",
          "value": "Yes"
        }
      ],
      "name": "Configuration tab group"
    }
  ],
